2026-04-14T01:34:14.632Z JOT-0039-9A comment.added "[x] Implemented three fixes: (1) due rendering keeps the year (Long mode YYYY-MM-DD; Short mode MM-DD for current year, YYYY-MM-DD otherwise); input parser accepts MM-DD (current year), DD.MM (current year), DD.MM.YYYY, on top of the existing YYYY-MM-DD plus today/tomorrow. (2) ls column order is now ID [PRIORITY] [DUE] TITLE [ASSIGNEE] [TAGS], tags rendered plain (no '#') in the rightmost column, assignee directly to its left. (3) '-a' and '--assignee' alias '--assign' on add and edit; 'jot add ... -a claude@joy' and 'jot edit 1 -a member' both work. bats grows four scenarios covering the year preservation, the new input shortcuts, the tag/assignee column order, and the -a shortcut." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
